Let me get your door.

255
00:20:08,874 --> 00:20:10,171
Buckle up.

256
00:20:16,081 --> 00:20:17,708
His name was Pencil.

257
00:20:17,816 --> 00:20:19,579
'Cause when I got him,
he was thin as a pencil

258
00:20:19,685 --> 00:20:21,812
and, you know, he was brown.

259
00:20:21,920 --> 00:20:23,581
Sounds really cute.

260
00:20:23,689 --> 00:20:27,250
Also, he did the sweetest little thing
with his paw.

261
00:20:27,359 --> 00:20:29,156
He would wipe it
on the floor back and forth,

262
00:20:29,261 --> 00:20:32,822
like he was trying to write
something to me.

263
00:20:32,931 --> 00:20:35,263
He had a really unique personality.

264
00:20:35,367 --> 00:20:37,164
Was he a water dog?

265
00:20:37,269 --> 00:20:38,600
Not really.

266
00:20:39,504 --> 00:20:42,234
So, you were saying you had a dog
who died when you were young?

267
00:20:42,341 --> 00:20:45,572
Tessie. I loved that dog.

268
00:20:45,677 --> 00:20:48,510
I had her since she was a puppy.
We did everything together.

269
00:20:48,614 --> 00:20:50,707
She was my right-hand bitch.

270
00:20:51,550 --> 00:20:55,452
Sorry. I mean in the dog way
of being a bitch.

271
00:20:56,555 --> 00:21:00,047
Yeah, she died way too young.
She was only six.

272
00:21:01,226 --> 00:21:02,193
Yeah.

273
00:21:04,563 --> 00:21:06,360
How did she die?

274
00:21:07,599 --> 00:21:10,500
I shot her in Wyoming.

275
00:21:10,602 --> 00:21:12,695
You want some more wine?

276
00:21:12,804 --> 00:21:14,738
Wait. What do you mean?

277
00:21:14,840 --> 00:21:18,298
It was an accident. A hunting accident.

278
00:21:18,410 --> 00:21:19,399
Oh.

279
00:21:19,511 --> 00:21:21,570
I still feel terrible.

280
00:21:24,116 --> 00:21:25,981
And what were you hunting?

281
00:21:26,084 --> 00:21:29,019
Hunting moose. Mooses.

282
00:21:30,289 --> 00:21:32,484
They got a lot of moose up there.
Don't worry about it.

283
00:21:34,626 --> 00:21:36,992
- You ever been hunting?
- No.

284
00:21:37,095 --> 00:21:39,120
It can be a rush.

285
00:21:39,231 --> 00:21:42,723
But, you know, accidents do happen,

286
00:21:42,834 --> 00:21:45,928
and, you know,
a gun is a very powerful weapon.

287
00:21:46,038 --> 00:21:47,869
I learned that the hard way.

288
00:21:47,973 --> 00:21:50,567
That's why I never
keep guns in my house.

289
00:21:51,910 --> 00:21:53,901
- Well, that's good.
- Yeah.

290
00:21:54,012 --> 00:21:56,344
Just knives. That's it.

291
00:22:10,028 --> 00:22:14,226
Thank you. I had a nice time.

292
00:22:14,333 --> 00:22:16,597
So, you ever been married?

293
00:22:16,702 --> 00:22:18,226
No. No.

294
00:22:19,204 --> 00:22:20,933
I mean, I was...

295
00:22:22,107 --> 00:22:24,769
I had boyfriends, but I never, you know.

296
00:22:24,876 --> 00:22:26,104
I guess I never...

297
00:22:26,211 --> 00:22:29,044
That never happened, but...

298
00:22:29,147 --> 00:22:33,345
You know, I think some people
just aren't as, you know...

299
00:22:34,653 --> 00:22:35,677
I don't even know what I'm saying.

300
00:22:35,787 --> 00:22:38,051
Just, you know, whatever, you know.
What are you gonna do?

301
00:22:38,156 --> 00:22:43,594
And the whole dating thing is just
kind of... Yuck, no thank you, so...

302
00:22:43,695 --> 00:22:48,223
Yeah, so that's basically
how I feel. Just, you know...

303
00:22:48,333 --> 00:22:49,493
I don't know.

304
00:22:49,601 --> 00:22:52,934
Just like that, I guess. But...

305
00:22:54,940 --> 00:22:57,101
So you wanna get the tour?

306
00:23:02,147 --> 00:23:04,877
It can be a real addiction.

307
00:23:04,983 --> 00:23:07,952
You know, some people spend
all kinds of money traveling the world

308
00:23:08,053 --> 00:23:09,418
just to find something to shoot

309
00:23:09,521 --> 00:23:12,752
that's new and hard to find, you know?

310
00:23:12,858 --> 00:23:16,225
Like leopards, rare birds and...

311
00:23:16,328 --> 00:23:20,196
And they have tours in Africa
and Asia and India.

312
00:23:20,298 --> 00:23:22,289
Even endangered species.

313
00:23:22,401 --> 00:23:24,266
You know, so you can get one
before they're all gone.

314
00:23:32,244 --> 00:23:34,712
This was a lucky shot.

315
00:23:34,813 --> 00:23:36,440
Isn't it a beauty?

316
00:23:38,049 --> 00:23:40,313
And those are my knives.

317
00:23:47,526 --> 00:23:49,517
Can I see your garage?

318
00:23:49,628 --> 00:23:50,925
My garage?

319
00:23:52,731 --> 00:23:55,495
Sure. Yeah, right through here.

320
00:24:00,272 --> 00:24:02,502
Was this open the other night?

321
00:24:02,607 --> 00:24:03,665
What?

322
00:24:03,775 --> 00:24:05,265
This garage door was open, wasn't it,

323
00:24:05,377 --> 00:24:07,140
the night that Pencil got sick?

324
00:24:07,245 --> 00:24:08,735
Yeah. Could be.

325
00:24:11,983 --> 00:24:13,951
What are you looking for?

326
00:24:16,455 --> 00:24:20,084
- Do you keep antifreeze in here?
- Yeah, I have.

327
00:24:20,192 --> 00:24:22,160
I don't know if I have any now, but...

328
00:24:22,260 --> 00:24:24,285
What about rat poison?

329
00:24:25,363 --> 00:24:26,523
No.

330
00:24:28,099 --> 00:24:29,361
No?

331
00:24:29,468 --> 00:24:31,868
Why? You got a rat problem?

332
00:24:44,683 --> 00:24:47,652
Are you looking for something?
Can I help you?

333
00:24:59,364 --> 00:25:00,797
I like you.

334
00:25:02,033 --> 00:25:04,365
What are you doing? Don't do that.

335
00:25:04,469 --> 00:25:06,096
- What? I was just...
- Stay away from me.

336
00:25:06,204 --> 00:25:07,694
- Don't do that.
- No, I was just...

337
00:25:07,806 --> 00:25:10,331
Come on. I gotta go.

338
00:25:42,674 --> 00:25:46,269
So, how was your date?

339
00:25:47,612 --> 00:25:49,011
He's not my type.

340
00:25:49,114 --> 00:25:52,242
Well, what is your type?
Do you have a type?

341
00:25:53,852 --> 00:25:56,912
I kind of have
a lot of work to do right now.

342
00:26:15,974 --> 00:26:17,100
Hello.

343
00:26:18,043 --> 00:26:19,943
<i>- Is this Miss Spade?
- Yes.</i>

344
00:26:20,045 --> 00:26:23,378
Hi, Miss Spade.
I'm Newt Erdrich at the SPCA L.A.

345
00:26:24,449 --> 00:26:26,474
I'm a Client Services Manager.

346
00:26:26,585 --> 00:26:29,213
<i>I work in the adoption program
to place animals</i>

347
00:26:29,321 --> 00:26:31,152
<i>to prevent them
from being euthanized by the city,</i>

348
00:26:31,256 --> 00:26:34,487
<i>and I noticed that you were very upset
about losing your dog.</i>

349
00:26:34,593 --> 00:26:39,326
And my instinct is that you're
a very sensitive, caring pet owner,

350
00:26:39,431 --> 00:26:42,889
and that is exactly
the kind of people that we're looking for.

351
00:26:43,001 --> 00:26:47,461
And, well, we have a dog here
who needs a home.

352
00:26:47,572 --> 00:26:52,942
<i>And this dog, Valentine is his name,</i>

353
00:26:53,044 --> 00:26:55,842
<i>has some behavioral issues,</i>

354
00:26:55,947 --> 00:26:58,711
and I just thought that maybe you might
fall in love with him.

355
00:26:58,817 --> 00:27:00,148
It's a shot in the dark here,

356
00:27:00,251 --> 00:27:03,152
but I'm just desperate
because I don't want to see him die.

357
00:27:03,254 --> 00:27:04,915
But no pressure.

358
00:27:10,962 --> 00:27:13,192
This is King.
He's diabetic, unfortunately.

359
00:27:13,298 --> 00:27:14,959
Aren't you? Big goof.

360
00:27:15,066 --> 00:27:18,331
- And this is Myrtle.
- Myrtle!

361
00:27:18,436 --> 00:27:21,701
She came in
when I was first starting at the Center.

362
00:27:21,806 --> 00:27:23,433
And who's this?

363
00:27:23,541 --> 00:27:24,906
That's Buttons.

364
00:27:25,010 --> 00:27:26,307
Oh, my God.

365
00:27:26,411 --> 00:27:28,242
And of course, this is Valentine.

366
00:27:28,346 --> 00:27:29,438
Now, I've kept him in the pen

367
00:27:29,547 --> 00:27:32,880
because he still isn't
playing well with others.

368
00:27:32,984 --> 00:27:34,042
Easy.

369
00:27:36,388 --> 00:27:40,552
I brought him home because,
you know, he spoke to me.

370
00:27:40,659 --> 00:27:42,593
And that happens sometimes.

371
00:27:42,694 --> 00:27:43,922
But I can't keep him

372
00:27:44,029 --> 00:27:47,829
because legally
you're only allowed three pets.

373
00:27:47,932 --> 00:27:51,595
Animals are like us, they live for love.

374
00:27:51,703 --> 00:27:54,103
And if you have too many of them,

375
00:27:54,205 --> 00:27:57,732
then there's not enough love
to go around, right?

376
00:27:58,543 --> 00:28:00,443
Valentine, say hello
to your new mommy.

377
00:28:05,083 --> 00:28:06,641
Listen, he's been abused,

378
00:28:06,751 --> 00:28:09,015
so you're really gonna
have to work with him.

379
00:28:09,120 --> 00:28:11,281
But look at his eyes.

380
00:28:11,389 --> 00:28:13,823
There's an old soul in there, I think.

381
00:28:15,460 --> 00:28:18,361
I just love him so much already.

382
00:28:18,463 --> 00:28:20,226
Well, if you need help training him,

383
00:28:20,331 --> 00:28:23,391
I do that part-time on the weekends.

384
00:28:23,501 --> 00:28:26,265
- And my methods are very positive.
- Okay.

385
00:28:26,371 --> 00:28:29,067
It's about reward,
it's not about punishment.

386
00:28:41,920 --> 00:28:44,684
Good boy. You like that...

387
00:28:46,825 --> 00:28:49,293
Down, Valentine! Down, Valentine!

388
00:28:49,394 --> 00:28:51,328
Down! Down!

389
00:28:59,804 --> 00:29:01,465
Peggy.

390
00:29:01,573 --> 00:29:03,040
Layla!

391
00:29:05,410 --> 00:29:07,310
Oh, Layla!

392
00:29:07,412 --> 00:29:09,243
I guess all my whining paid off.

393
00:29:09,347 --> 00:29:11,281
Oh, my gosh!

394
00:29:11,382 --> 00:29:13,077
I totally was not prepared.

395
00:29:13,184 --> 00:29:16,119
<i>We went to go see
the new Spider-Man... Superman...</i>

396
00:29:16,221 --> 00:29:18,849
<i>No, no, no! Spider-Man.
Anyway, it was cute.</i>

397
00:29:18,957 --> 00:29:22,154
So then we went
to Greenstein's Deli. Not romantic.

398
00:29:22,260 --> 00:29:24,490
And he's acting all weird and nervous,

399
00:29:24,596 --> 00:29:26,325
and I'm like, "What is going on?"

400
00:29:26,431 --> 00:29:29,923
And then, bam! He just pulls it out!

401
00:29:30,034 --> 00:29:31,865
And I'm not even pregnant!

402
00:29:31,970 --> 00:29:33,597
It's kind of a mellow engagement.

403
00:29:33,705 --> 00:29:34,865
That's what Don's calling it.

404
00:29:34,973 --> 00:29:36,838
But we'll see.

405
00:29:36,941 --> 00:29:38,806
Guess what?
I have some good news, too.

406
00:29:38,910 --> 00:29:41,401
Oh. What, what, what?

407
00:29:41,513 --> 00:29:43,140
I got another dog.

408
00:29:44,349 --> 00:29:47,910
It's a shelter dog,
and his name's Valentine.

409
00:29:48,019 --> 00:29:50,351
Peggy, how are you ever
gonna find a boyfriend,

410
00:29:50,455 --> 00:29:53,151
if you keep shacking up with dogs?

411
00:30:00,431 --> 00:30:01,864
Do you have any soy milk?

412
00:30:01,966 --> 00:30:06,062
- I'm sorry, I don't.
- That's okay. It's okay.

413
00:30:07,071 --> 00:30:08,436
It's very political.

414
00:30:08,540 --> 00:30:10,030
Because on the one hand
you have the city,

415
00:30:10,141 --> 00:30:12,871
and they want to terminate every animal
they get their hands on.

416
00:30:12,977 --> 00:30:14,968
- Yeah, they just have a killing routine.
- Wow.

417
00:30:15,079 --> 00:30:17,138
And I know for a fact

418
00:30:17,248 --> 00:30:20,706
that they have paper products
stored in those cages.

419
00:30:20,819 --> 00:30:23,982
I could write an exposé.
It would explode like a bomb.

420
00:30:24,088 --> 00:30:26,818
And on the other hand,
you have the animal activists,

421
00:30:26,925 --> 00:30:29,018
who don't wanna see
even one animal die.

422
00:30:29,127 --> 00:30:31,789
And we come under criticism
because we work with the city,

423
00:30:31,896 --> 00:30:35,093
but there are 5,000 kittens that come
through the system each year.

424
00:30:35,200 --> 00:30:36,758
You can't save them all, right?

425
00:30:36,868 --> 00:30:39,234
Wow. That must be
so much pressure for you.

426
00:30:39,337 --> 00:30:42,272
And I have nightmares, you know?

427
00:30:42,373 --> 00:30:44,807
I had a nightmare last night

428
00:30:44,909 --> 00:30:47,400
that I was being attacked

429
00:30:49,480 --> 00:30:52,847
and raped by two bull mastiffs.

430
00:30:56,020 --> 00:30:58,750
And... But what am
I supposed to do? Stop caring?

431
00:30:58,857 --> 00:31:01,417
Oh, no. I mean, you can't stop caring.

432
00:31:01,526 --> 00:31:03,426
This is your passion.

433
00:31:03,528 --> 00:31:05,257
- Right.
- You know.

434
00:31:05,363 --> 00:31:06,796
Makes sense to me.

435
00:31:06,898 --> 00:31:08,331
You're right.

436
00:31:11,035 --> 00:31:13,868
Good boy. Eyes to me.

437
00:31:13,972 --> 00:31:16,133
Eyes to me. He knows.

438
00:31:16,241 --> 00:31:18,937
And big ups. Big ups.

439
00:31:19,811 --> 00:31:20,778
Okay.

440
00:31:22,313 --> 00:31:24,110
No, no, no.

441
00:31:24,215 --> 00:31:27,651
He needs to know
he can't play that part.

442
00:31:27,752 --> 00:31:30,721
When I was little, we had a Lhasa Apso.

443
00:31:35,293 --> 00:31:36,590
Valentine.

444
00:31:49,474 --> 00:31:52,102
That's good. That's good.

445
00:31:52,210 --> 00:31:55,668
You can just sign your name there.

446
00:31:59,817 --> 00:32:02,513
You know,
I've always had better relationships

447
00:32:02,620 --> 00:32:05,418
with animals than people.

448
00:32:05,523 --> 00:32:07,252
I can relate.

449
00:32:07,358 --> 00:32:09,851
Animals aren't petty, for one.

450
00:32:09,961 --> 00:32:12,293
They don't backstab you.

451
00:32:12,997 --> 00:32:15,966
So what about girlfriends
and that sort of thing?

452
00:32:16,067 --> 00:32:19,798
Oh, I don't know.
That's very complicated.

453
00:32:21,506 --> 00:32:25,340
I was raised in a very...

454
00:32:27,045 --> 00:32:28,205
Culty...

455
00:32:29,414 --> 00:32:31,006
Adults being...

456
00:32:32,150 --> 00:32:34,584
Very... No boundaries.

457
00:32:36,220 --> 00:32:38,780
I just used to go off by myself...

458
00:32:38,890 --> 00:32:44,157
And I always had
this connection with animals.

459
00:32:44,262 --> 00:32:45,695
And that's why I'm a vegan.

460
00:32:45,797 --> 00:32:48,664
People say, "If you couldn't kill it,
you shouldn't eat it. "

461
00:32:48,766 --> 00:32:51,667
And I could never kill an animal.

462
00:32:51,769 --> 00:32:53,202
I understand.

463
00:33:25,003 --> 00:33:26,800
I'm so excited to be eating here.

464
00:33:26,904 --> 00:33:29,532
There's a couple of things
that are really amazing.

465
00:33:29,640 --> 00:33:34,543
The seitan Sloppy Joe.
The tempeh BLT is good.

466
00:33:34,645 --> 00:33:36,408
Tofu chop.

467
00:33:36,514 --> 00:33:38,209
One of everything.

468
00:33:38,316 --> 00:33:39,806
No, not really.

469
00:33:43,254 --> 00:33:46,587
I think a veggie pizza.

470
00:33:49,861 --> 00:33:50,919
What?

471
00:33:51,696 --> 00:33:52,890
Nothing.

472
00:34:25,763 --> 00:34:27,663
Do you sleep with your dogs?

473
00:34:27,765 --> 00:34:28,857
Guilty.

474
00:34:28,966 --> 00:34:31,594
- Three dogs?
- Yeah, it gets crowded.

475
00:34:31,702 --> 00:34:34,762
King hogs the covers. Don't you, King?

476
00:34:36,774 --> 00:34:38,765
Wipe that grin off your face.

477
00:34:43,514 --> 00:34:47,746
You know, it's really nice
to finally meet someone who just...

478
00:34:47,852 --> 00:34:52,152
I don't know,
I think we have a lot in common.

479
00:34:52,256 --> 00:34:54,622
And you've really
opened my eyes to so many different...

480
00:34:54,725 --> 00:34:56,716
- Oh, I think you're great.
- Yeah?

481
00:34:56,828 --> 00:34:58,693
Yeah. Definitely.

482
00:35:03,734 --> 00:35:06,862
Well, thanks.

483
00:35:06,971 --> 00:35:08,632
- And you know what?
- What?

484
00:35:08,739 --> 00:35:10,172
I'm gonna be a vegan.

485
00:35:10,274 --> 00:35:11,502
Really?

486
00:35:11,642 --> 00:35:12,540
Yeah?

487
00:35:12,643 --> 00:35:15,373
I mean, after reading all those books,
how can I not? Absolutely.

488
00:35:15,480 --> 00:35:17,607
Well, I think that's great.

489
00:35:17,715 --> 00:35:18,807
Yeah.

490
00:35:48,779 --> 00:35:51,304
It's been a while since I...

491
00:35:52,617 --> 00:35:53,948
I'm just...

492
00:35:55,353 --> 00:35:58,220
Well, we don't have to do anything.

493
00:35:59,257 --> 00:36:01,122
Oh. Okay.

494
00:36:13,504 --> 00:36:14,562
Cupcakes!

495
00:36:14,672 --> 00:36:16,071
These look diabolical.

496
00:36:16,174 --> 00:36:18,074
I just had a Croissan'Wich.

