Yes.

1017
01:12:07,919 --> 01:12:11,047
Ma'am, you can't adopt 15 dogs.
The limit is three.

1018
01:12:11,155 --> 01:12:14,215
Well, I work for the ASPCA L.A.

1019
01:12:14,325 --> 01:12:17,385
I work for Newt Erdrich.
He's a client services manager.

1020
01:12:17,495 --> 01:12:19,224
I happen to be in the adoption program,

1021
01:12:19,330 --> 01:12:20,422
and I will be taking all these dogs

1022
01:12:20,531 --> 01:12:22,897
and placing them in adoption situations,

1023
01:12:23,000 --> 01:12:25,969
so I think that should be fine, then,
thank you.

1024
01:12:28,673 --> 01:12:30,834
Get me the dogs. Great.

1025
01:12:52,230 --> 01:12:55,063
Come on, you two with me.
You two with me. In the house.

1026
01:12:59,103 --> 01:13:01,799
Quiet! I will be right back!

1027
01:13:09,347 --> 01:13:13,477
Big dogs out. Come on.
No, no, big dogs out.

1028
01:13:13,584 --> 01:13:15,984
Out, out, out, out, out.

1029
01:13:18,656 --> 01:13:20,385
No! Oh, no!

1030
01:13:20,491 --> 01:13:23,016
No, no, no, no, no, no, no, no.

1031
01:13:51,556 --> 01:13:53,649
Here's some water for you.

1032
01:13:53,758 --> 01:13:55,385
Oh, good boys.

1033
01:13:55,493 --> 01:13:56,619
No fighting!

1034
01:13:56,727 --> 01:14:00,219
Mommy's gotta go to work.
Mommy's gotta go to work.

1035
01:14:00,331 --> 01:14:03,027
Okay. Be good.

1036
01:14:03,134 --> 01:14:04,863
Oh, no. Mommy's late. Mommy's late.

1037
01:14:04,969 --> 01:14:07,062
You be good. Be good. Be good.

1038
01:14:07,171 --> 01:14:09,002
Mommy's late for work.

1039
01:14:09,907 --> 01:14:12,637
Peggy! Robin's been
looking for you for an hour.

1040
01:14:12,743 --> 01:14:14,438
He seems pretty agitated.

1041
01:14:14,545 --> 01:14:16,513
- Where is he?
- He's in a meeting now with Jeff.

1042
01:14:22,687 --> 01:14:24,245
<i>- Hello.
- Hey, Peg?</i>

1043
01:14:24,355 --> 01:14:25,413
<i>Why didn't you tell us</i>

1044
01:14:25,523 --> 01:14:28,321
<i>you took Lissie to some animal farm
and indoctrinated her?</i>

1045
01:14:28,426 --> 01:14:29,757
Well, she wanted to see
her chicken, Pier.

1046
01:14:29,861 --> 01:14:30,828
I thought it would be nice.

1047
01:14:30,928 --> 01:14:33,726
<i>No, it's not nice. She's traumatized.</i>

1048
01:14:33,831 --> 01:14:35,230
Well, I'm sorry that you feel that way.

1049
01:14:35,333 --> 01:14:38,359
<i>- Traumatized, Peggy!
- No, I don't think she's traumatized.</i>

1050
01:14:38,469 --> 01:14:40,198
<i>She will not even eat
a ham sandwich now.</i>

1051
01:14:40,304 --> 01:14:42,636
Well, what's so important
about eating a ham sandwich, anyway?

1052
01:14:42,740 --> 01:14:44,207
If she doesn't want to eat it...

1053
01:14:44,308 --> 01:14:46,276
You know, Peggy,
you've completely betrayed our trust!

1054
01:14:46,377 --> 01:14:47,708
<i>- The furs.
- Well, I'm sorry you feel that way.</i>

1055
01:14:47,812 --> 01:14:50,440
<i>- Yeah. And Bret can't find her furs.
- What?</i>

1056
01:14:50,548 --> 01:14:52,209
What, you think I stole her furs?

1057
01:14:52,316 --> 01:14:55,149
<i>- Peggy, where are they?
- I have no idea!</i>

1058
01:14:55,253 --> 01:14:58,347
Look, I have to go right now. I'm at work.

1059
01:14:58,456 --> 01:14:59,821
She hung up.

1060
01:15:04,061 --> 01:15:06,723
Hey, Peggy, Robin's looking for you.

1061
01:15:06,831 --> 01:15:09,800
What happened to you? You okay?

1062
01:15:11,669 --> 01:15:14,229
Peggy, I know you're
gonna be disappointed,

1063
01:15:14,338 --> 01:15:15,999
but it's not working out with Snowball.

1064
01:15:18,543 --> 01:15:23,071
He keeps peeing all over the place
and chewing up all the furniture.

1065
01:15:23,180 --> 01:15:25,478
- And Don, he thinks that...
- Don?

1066
01:15:29,086 --> 01:15:33,216
Layla, do you understand that that dog
will be loyal to you his whole life?

1067
01:15:33,324 --> 01:15:35,417
Don's not even loyal to you now.

1068
01:15:36,260 --> 01:15:38,854
Don wants to keep it.

1069
01:15:38,963 --> 01:15:40,157
It's me.

1070
01:15:41,732 --> 01:15:43,757
What do you mean,
he's not loyal to me?

1071
01:15:47,705 --> 01:15:49,764
What, Peggy? Say it.

1072
01:15:51,342 --> 01:15:53,333
I didn't mean anything.

1073
01:15:53,444 --> 01:15:56,345
I gotta... I gotta go.
Robin's looking for me.

1074
01:16:03,187 --> 01:16:05,212
So, I just got a call this morning

1075
01:16:05,323 --> 01:16:08,451
from a woman named
Jocelyn Kleinhoffer.

1076
01:16:09,860 --> 01:16:13,352
She works for
the Animal Action something.

1077
01:16:13,464 --> 01:16:17,560
She wanted to thank me
for my generous contribution of $200

1078
01:16:17,668 --> 01:16:21,729
to help prevent
the clubbing of baby seals in Canada.

1079
01:16:25,676 --> 01:16:28,668
I trusted you
with the most valuable thing I have,

1080
01:16:28,779 --> 01:16:31,577
and you stole from me.

1081
01:16:35,252 --> 01:16:38,653
I thought we were
on the same team, but...

1082
01:16:40,691 --> 01:16:42,420
I trusted you.

1083
01:16:45,162 --> 01:16:47,153
So what were you thinking?

1084
01:17:02,613 --> 01:17:04,046
You're fired.

1085
01:17:07,251 --> 01:17:09,185
Effective immediately.

1086
01:17:39,717 --> 01:17:42,743
I have not slept 10 minutes in a week!

1087
01:17:42,853 --> 01:17:44,445
How many dogs do you have in there?

1088
01:17:44,555 --> 01:17:46,182
They need a home.

1089
01:17:46,290 --> 01:17:48,952
Well, get them one,
so I don't have to put up with this racket.

1090
01:17:49,060 --> 01:17:50,254
Not now!

1091
01:17:50,361 --> 01:17:52,522
And do you know
how much this house stinks?

1092
01:17:52,630 --> 01:17:55,098
You know what? You're a jerk.

1093
01:17:55,199 --> 01:17:58,566
I'm telling you,
you deal with this or I will.

1094
01:18:34,238 --> 01:18:36,297
<i>- Hello.
- Peggy, it's Newt.</i>

1095
01:18:36,907 --> 01:18:38,932
I haven't heard from you.
Are you still mad at me?

1096
01:18:39,043 --> 01:18:40,772
No, I'm not mad.

1097
01:18:42,613 --> 01:18:44,171
What's all that noise?

1098
01:18:45,516 --> 01:18:46,710
My dogs.

1099
01:18:46,917 --> 01:18:49,112
Oh, you got new dogs? That's great.

1100
01:18:50,354 --> 01:18:52,982
- Where did you get them?
- From the pound.

1101
01:18:53,791 --> 01:18:57,454
You sound weird, Peggy.
Is everything all right?

1102
01:18:58,229 --> 01:19:02,928
I was just thinking, you know, just now,
my house is full of love.

1103
01:19:04,535 --> 01:19:09,336
I have too much love in my life.
I've never had that before.

1104
01:19:10,040 --> 01:19:13,066
- Come here.
- Peggy? Peggy?

1105
01:20:44,969 --> 01:20:48,063
Well, I want them back! I don't care!

1106
01:20:49,206 --> 01:20:52,107
Well, what are you gonna do with them?

1107
01:20:52,209 --> 01:20:54,177
Well, you know what, ma'am?
That is not good enough!

1108
01:20:54,278 --> 01:20:56,405
I want a record
of every one of those dogs,

1109
01:20:56,513 --> 01:21:00,449
and if even one of those dogs is hurt,
I am hiring a lawyer!

1110
01:21:00,551 --> 01:21:02,246
Who called you?

1111
01:21:02,353 --> 01:21:03,342
Well, you know what?

1112
01:21:03,454 --> 01:21:05,445
You don't have to tell me who called
because my neighbor called!

1113
01:21:05,556 --> 01:21:07,217
Can I have your name please, ma'am?

1114
01:21:07,324 --> 01:21:08,348
Can I...

1115
01:21:08,459 --> 01:21:10,051
Don't hang up on me!

1116
01:21:16,533 --> 01:21:17,659
Hello!

1117
01:21:21,272 --> 01:21:22,637
Hello!

1118
01:22:34,311 --> 01:22:36,302
<i>You ever been hunting?</i>

1119
01:22:37,381 --> 01:22:38,973
<i>It can be a rush.</i>

1120
01:22:40,250 --> 01:22:44,482
<i>You gotta be real quiet,
so you can hear a twig snap.</i>

1121
01:22:44,588 --> 01:22:48,422
<i>After hours of waiting, sometimes,</i>

1122
01:22:48,525 --> 01:22:50,823
<i>up comes a moose</i>

1123
01:22:50,928 --> 01:22:53,863
<i>or a Rocky Mountain elk.</i>

1124
01:22:56,300 --> 01:22:59,963
<i>And there's nothing like the feeling like</i>

1125
01:23:00,070 --> 01:23:02,300
<i>something's gonna happen.</i>

1126
01:23:03,440 --> 01:23:06,603
<i>You know, but it don't know.</i>

1127
01:23:07,478 --> 01:23:10,504
<i>It's just another moment in its life,</i>

1128
01:23:10,614 --> 01:23:13,947
<i>but you know it's its last,
its last moment.</i>

1129
01:23:14,952 --> 01:23:17,147
<i>And you're gonna take it.</i>

1130
01:23:28,332 --> 01:23:33,031
Yeah, so then she started to hang out
with that girl Linda and Kimmy.

1131
01:23:33,137 --> 01:23:34,570
You know,
the one with that thing in her lip.

1132
01:23:34,671 --> 01:23:35,797
Oh, yeah, that piercing.

1133
01:23:35,906 --> 01:23:38,932
And they just had her
partying like crazy.

1134
01:23:39,043 --> 01:23:40,601
Bad news.

1135
01:23:40,711 --> 01:23:43,737
So she left Jamie after that

1136
01:23:43,847 --> 01:23:45,542
and decided
she wanted to be with Dale.

1137
01:23:46,850 --> 01:23:49,216
But Dale was in the military.

1138
01:23:49,319 --> 01:23:51,310
That's why she divorced him.

1139
01:23:51,422 --> 01:23:54,858
Then she got with Darryl.
Half-Japanese, by the way.

1140
01:23:54,958 --> 01:23:56,619
And then they had a kid.

1141
01:24:03,767 --> 01:24:04,927
Al.

1142
01:24:07,204 --> 01:24:09,104
I think we've been robbed.

1143
01:24:09,206 --> 01:24:10,571
What? What do you mean?

1144
01:24:10,674 --> 01:24:12,539
I think you've been robbed!

1145
01:24:18,715 --> 01:24:20,307
Are you crazy!

1146
01:24:21,985 --> 01:24:24,545
- Call 911!
- Let go of me!

1147
01:24:33,330 --> 01:24:34,388
...can stay downstairs.

1148
01:24:34,498 --> 01:24:36,591
This bedroom needs to be
painted for her.

1149
01:24:36,700 --> 01:24:38,861
Kind of something soothing...

1150
01:24:44,374 --> 01:24:47,605
Hey, Lissie, sweetie,
it's night-night time.

1151
01:24:57,287 --> 01:25:00,017
The lawyer thinks because
she didn't actually hurt anybody,

1152
01:25:00,124 --> 01:25:01,785
it's gonna be all right.

1153
01:25:01,892 --> 01:25:04,190
And I talked to her boss for a long time.

1154
01:25:04,294 --> 01:25:06,091
He says,
because of their years together,

1155
01:25:06,196 --> 01:25:09,529
that if she gets help
and pays what she stole,

1156
01:25:09,633 --> 01:25:12,568
he's willing to give her job back.

1157
01:25:18,642 --> 01:25:22,305
Peggy, what were you thinking?

1158
01:25:28,385 --> 01:25:32,913
I just wanted him to know
what it felt like to...

1159
01:25:37,294 --> 01:25:39,854
What it felt like to what?

1160
01:25:43,600 --> 01:25:45,568
To be hunted.

1161
01:25:46,570 --> 01:25:48,231
Oh, Peggy.

1162
01:25:49,706 --> 01:25:51,697
We love you.

1163
01:25:52,609 --> 01:25:55,169
And we're so worried about you.

1164
01:25:57,147 --> 01:26:01,015
We're gonna get you the help you need.
We're here for you.

1165
01:26:37,988 --> 01:26:39,148
Lissie.

1166
01:26:40,857 --> 01:26:42,586
I'm so sorry.

1167
01:26:44,494 --> 01:26:45,654
Why?

1168
01:26:49,666 --> 01:26:52,362
You love animals,
don't you, Aunt Peggy?

1169
01:26:55,706 --> 01:26:57,196
So do I.

1170
01:27:00,711 --> 01:27:03,942
This one's mean and this one's nice.

1171
01:27:23,834 --> 01:27:26,667
Oh, welcome back, Peggy.

1172
01:27:30,941 --> 01:27:32,772
There she is.

1173
01:27:38,749 --> 01:27:41,980
Here, Peggy. Welcome back.

1174
01:27:42,085 --> 01:27:44,178
You look so pretty.

1175
01:27:46,757 --> 01:27:49,055
I had a talk with Jeff.

1176
01:27:49,159 --> 01:27:53,357
He moved us to the orange team
with Brad and Denise.

1177
01:27:54,498 --> 01:27:57,228
I just think that's a better fit.

1178
01:27:57,334 --> 01:28:00,735
Denise is great with people,
Brad's good with strategy,

1179
01:28:00,837 --> 01:28:02,771
and I'm the numbers guy.

1180
01:28:04,374 --> 01:28:06,433
Snowball! No!

1181
01:28:07,978 --> 01:28:09,070
You'll find this amusing.

1182
01:28:09,179 --> 01:28:12,012
Your friend Layla couldn't find anyone
to take her dog, so I took it.

1183
01:28:12,115 --> 01:28:15,846
I don't know what came over me.
Momentary lapse of reason.

1184
01:28:19,056 --> 01:28:23,425
I hate leaving him home all day,
so I sneak him in sometimes.

1185
01:28:23,527 --> 01:28:26,291
I don't really like the name,
but he answers to it.

1186
01:28:26,396 --> 01:28:30,196
Okay, Snowball. Down. There you go.

1187
01:28:32,169 --> 01:28:33,864
Stay over there.

1188
01:28:38,141 --> 01:28:39,540
Anyway.

1189
01:28:40,811 --> 01:28:43,371
So where were we? Oh, yeah.

1190
01:28:43,480 --> 01:28:45,311
The orange team.

1191
01:29:14,010 --> 01:29:16,501
Hey. Guess what?

1192
01:29:16,613 --> 01:29:19,878
We finally have a date. June 21st.

1193
01:29:20,784 --> 01:29:22,149
That's great, Layla.

1194
01:29:22,252 --> 01:29:25,221
Yeah, it took a lot of work,
that's for sure.

1195
01:29:25,322 --> 01:29:28,257
And I want you to be a bridesmaid.

1196
01:29:28,358 --> 01:29:31,384
You wanna go to lunch? Don has plans.

1197
01:29:31,495 --> 01:29:34,658
You know what? I can't.
I have a lot to catch up on.

1198
01:29:34,765 --> 01:29:38,257
I understand. I'll talk to you later, okay?

1199
01:30:19,609 --> 01:30:24,205
<i>If you all didn't think I was crazy,
I'm sure you will now.</i>

1200
01:30:24,314 --> 01:30:27,340
<i>How do I explain the things
I've said and done?</i>

1201
01:30:28,685 --> 01:30:31,848
<i>How do I explain
the person I've become?</i>

1202
01:30:35,759 --> 01:30:39,593
<i>I know I've disappointed everyone,
and I'm sorry for that.</i>

1203
01:30:41,264 --> 01:30:44,097
<i>I wish I was a more articulate person.</i>

1204
01:30:54,444 --> 01:30:57,607
<i>I believe life is magical.</i>

1205
01:30:57,714 --> 01:30:59,978
<i>It is so precious.</i>

1206
01:31:01,485 --> 01:31:05,319
<i>And there are
so many kinds of life in this life.</i>

1207
01:31:05,422 --> 01:31:07,847
<i>So many things to love.</i>

1208
01:31:16,733 --> 01:31:19,964
<i>The love for a husband or a wife,</i>

1209
01:31:20,070 --> 01:31:22,436
<i>a boyfriend or girlfriend.</i>

1210
01:31:25,308 --> 01:31:28,641
<i>The love for children.</i>

1211
01:31:28,745 --> 01:31:31,213
<i>The love for yourself.</i>

1212
01:31:32,482 --> 01:31:33,972
<i>And even material things.</i>

1213
01:31:39,189 --> 01:31:42,454
<i>This is my love. It is mine.</i>

1214
01:31:44,995 --> 01:31:48,487
<i>And it fills me and it defines me.</i>

1215
01:31:50,233 --> 01:31:52,531
<i>And it compels me on.</i>

